&lt;h1&gt;About Faropoint&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaningful Relationships. Ownership. Curiosity. &lt;/strong&gt;Tenacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Established in 2012, Faropoint is a pure play RE fund manager focusing on the last mile industrial sector. Having acquired more than 500 warehouses to date, it is the most active aggregator of warehouses in the US in the past five years. Our platform is built to harness the sector&#39;s fragmentation, operating through 7 regional offices with 120+ employees in vertically integrated teams enhanced by proprietary AI-driven tools, while benefiting from compelling fundamentals like constrained supply growth, reshoring, and e-commerce tailwinds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Job Summary&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Asset Management is responsible for full oversight of the regional portfolio, owning asset strategy, leasing decisions, and performance outcomes. This is a key leadership role within Faropoint&#39;s asset management organization, combining hands-on portfolio management with team leadership, strategic portfolio development, and investor relations. The Director will mentor asset management professionals, drive operational excellence across the portfolio, and ensure alignment of leasing, financial, and operational strategies with fund objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own all aspects of leasing relationships and decisions, including tenant negotiations, lease structuring, rent growth strategies, and lease renewals across the regional portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead leasing execution and strategy, setting market positioning, defining competitive advantages, and driving proactive tenant engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee due diligence and appraisal processes for new acquisitions, ensuring thorough analysis and alignment with fund underwriting standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee asset management teams responsible for budgets, forecasting, vendor relations, tenant relations, accounts receivable, and maintenance operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive portfolio strategy and performance reporting, conducting market analysis, identifying repositioning opportunities, and presenting portfolio performance to investors and fund leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and develop asset management team members, providing guidance on technical skills, market knowledge, and professional growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve all aspects of operational budgets, capital improvement plans, appraisals, and financial analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage vendor relationships and capital improvement initiatives, ensuring quality execution and cost control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead strategic initiatives to improve operational efficiency, implement process improvements, and leverage technology to drive portfolio performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with fund policies, loan covenants, and regulatory requirements across the regional portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-10 years of experience in asset management or real estate investment, with at least 3-5 years in a leadership or senior management capacity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record managing industrial/commercial real estate portfolios with demonstrated success in leasing, operational management, and financial performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Real Estate, Finance, Business Administration, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise in commercial real estate finance, including underwriting, ARGUS, rent roll analysis, and financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership and team development capabilities with experience managing and mentoring asset management professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, with ability to interface effectively with C-level executives, investors, and external partners&lt;/li&gt;
