&lt;p&gt;Established in 2012, Faropoint is a pure play RE fund manager focusing on the last mile industrial sector. Having acquired more than 500 warehouses to date, it is the most active aggregator of warehouses in the US in the past five years. Our platform is built to harness the sector’s fragmentation, operating through 7 regional offices with 120+ employees in vertically integrated teams enhanced by proprietary AI-driven tools, while benefiting from compelling fundamentals like constrained supply growth, reshoring, and e-commerce tailwinds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt; The Acquisitions Associate will play a key role in driving Faropoint&#39;s acquisition process across Florida markets. This position is responsible for deal sourcing and broker relationship management, underwriting, due diligence coordination, market research, and financial analysis, and will actively support the full investment lifecycle from initial opportunity identification through Investment Committee approval.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deal Sourcing &amp;amp; Broker Relationships:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Cultivate and maintain relationships with brokers, owners, and market participants to generate on-market and off-market acquisition opportunities across Florida markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Track and manage an active deal pipeline across multiple markets and strategies, ensuring disciplined follow-up, prioritization, and reporting on deal flow activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Underwriting &amp;amp; Financial Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Perform detailed underwriting of potential acquisition opportunities, including cash flow modeling, return analysis, sensitivity analysis, and risk assessment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due Diligence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Coordinate and manage the due diligence process on prospective acquisitions, including site visits, review of legal documents, and management of third-party consultants (environmental, engineering, title, legal).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Research:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Conduct comprehensive market research to identify trends, opportunities, and competitive dynamics across Florida&#39;s industrial commercial real estate sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Investment Committee Process:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Prepare detailed investment memos and supporting materials for senior leadership and Investment Committee presentations, and assist in managing IC timelines, Q&amp;amp;A, and approval workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Work closely with asset management, lenders, outside counsel, and third-party consultants to ensure seamless execution of acquisition strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Prepare regular reports and presentations on pipeline activity, market conditions, and financial performance for senior management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Real Estate, Business, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience in investment banking, private equity, commercial real estate, or a related institutional role.&lt;/li&gt;
